Job Summary

We are looking for an experienced Java Developer to be involved in large-scale projects to design, build and maintain enterprise and web applications.

Mandatory Skill-set
• Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology or equivalent;
• At least 3 years of experience in application design, development and maintenance;
• Strong technical experience in Java / J2EE technologies and frameworks i.e. JSP, Servlets, JSF, JSTL, Spring, Hibernate, Struts;
• Proficient in using SQL - MySQL, MS SQL and Oracle;
• Strong analytical skills and problem solving aptitude;
• Strong interpersonal, communication and written skill;
• Independent and good team player.

Desired Skill-set
• Experience in Agile processes.

Responsibilities
• Involved in designing, developing and supporting critical systems for the organization;
• Assist in gathering and analysis of business requirements and perform development on the various modules of the system;
• Involved system integration and... testing from System Integration (SIT) and User Acceptance Testing (UAT);
• Maintain, support and ensure necessary changes are implemented and documented;
• Provide user and system support during and post-implementation;
• Keep abreast of the latest technological trends and assess the feasibility of adopting new technologies.

Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest.

When you apply, you voluntarily consent to the disclosure, collection and use of your personal data for employment/recruitment and related purposes in accordance with the SCIENTE Group Privacy Policy, a copy of which is published at SCIENTE’s website (https://www.sciente.com/privacy-policy).

Confidentiality is assured, and only shortlisted candidates will be notified for interviews.

